<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="content-section alt-bg">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-label">FAQ</span>
      <h2>Common Questions</h2>
      <p>Get answers to frequently asked questions about AC service in Hawaii.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>What size AC unit do I need for my Hawaii home?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>The right AC size depends on your home's square footage, insulation, ceiling height, and sun exposure. In Hawaii's tropical climate, proper sizing is critical. Our technicians perform a load calculation to determine the ideal size for efficient cooling without wasting energy.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>How often should I service my AC in Hawaii?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>We recommend servicing your AC system at least once per year, ideally before the hot season. Hawaii's humid climate and salt air can be tough on equipment, so regular maintenance helps prevent breakdowns and keeps your system running efficiently.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>Do you offer same-day AC repair?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>Yes! We understand Hawaii's heat can be unbearable without AC. We offer same-day service for emergency repairs whenever possible. Call (808) 664-5751 to schedule your urgent repair.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>What brands of AC systems do you install?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>We install all major brands including Daikin, Mitsubishi, Carrier, Trane, and more. We'll help you choose the best system for your needs and budget, with options for mini-split ductless systems, central air, and heat pumps.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>Are mini-split systems good for Hawaii homes?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>Absolutely! Mini-split ductless systems are ideal for Hawaii. They're energy-efficient, don't require ductwork, allow zone control, and work perfectly in our climate. Many Hawaii homeowners prefer them for their flexibility and efficiency.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>Do you serve all of Oahu?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>Yes! We serve Kailua, Kaneohe, Honolulu, Pearl City, Ewa Beach, Aiea, Mililani, Wahiawa, and all surrounding areas across Oahu. Contact us to confirm service availability in your area.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

